                    {"id": "q3", "type": "multiple_choice", "question": "Case: A city's public transit ridership has declined 40% post-pandemic. Structure analysis of ridership recovery:", "options": ["Commuter vs Non-Commuter Trips, by Mode", "Frequency × Riders per Trip × Trip Distance", "Remote Work Impact, Safety Concerns, Service Changes, Alternative Transport", "Demand-Side (Rider Behavior), Supply-Side (Service Levels)"], "correct_index": 3, "correct_answer": "Demand-Side (Rider Behavior), Supply-Side (Service Levels)", "explanation": "Demand vs Supply is MECE for transit: Are people not wanting to ride (WFH, safety) or not able to ride (service cuts, reliability)? Then drill into specifics within each."},
